                            <div class="container">
                    <div class="exc-container">
                        <div class="muscle-text bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                            <h3><b>HamstringsÂ </b></h3><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK546688/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">hamstring muscle group</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> consists of three muscles located at the back of the thigh. These include the biceps femoris, semitendinosus, and semimembranosus.Â </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The biceps femoris are located toward the outside of the back of the thigh. The semitendinosus are in the middle to the inner part of the thigh. As for the semimembranosus, it is located on the thighâ€™s inner edge.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In a dumbbell Romanian deadlift, the hamstrings are the primary muscles involved. They play an important role in both the lifting and lowering phases.Â </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">During the lowering phase, the hamstrings eccentrically contract (lengthen under tension) to control the descent. Both the biceps femoris and semitendinosus have an </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8835508/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">activation rate of 45%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> during the lowering phase of the dumbbell RDL.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">During the lifting phase, the hamstrings concentrically contract (shorten under tension) to bring the torso back to the starting position. They are the main drivers responsible for the thrusting motion required to bring the torso back to the starting position.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">During this phase, the hamstring muscles have an activation rate ranging from </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8835508/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">75%â€“100%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
