                                    <div class="muscle-img">
                                        <img src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Errector-Spinae.png" alt="">
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="has-medium-font-size">Erector Spinae</p>
                                    <p class="has-small-font-size"><p><span data-sheets-root="\&quot;1\&quot;" data-sheets-value="\&quot;{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Muscles" data-sheets-userformat="\&quot;{&quot;2&quot;:769,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;11&quot;:3,&quot;12&quot;:0}\&quot;">Muscles that span the entire length of your spine on either side.</span></p></p>
                                </div>
                                                            <div class="secondary-item muscle-item">
                                    <div class="muscle-img">
                                        <img src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wrist-Flexors.png" alt="">
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="has-medium-font-size">Wrist Flexors</p>
                                    <p class="has-small-font-size"><p>Muscles that span the inside of your lower arm, between your elbow and wrist palm side up.</p></p>
                                </div>
                                                            <div class="secondary-item muscle-item">
                                    <div class="muscle-img">
                                        <img src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wrist-Extensors.png" alt="">
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="has-medium-font-size">Wrist Extensors</p>
                                    <p class="has-small-font-size"><p>Muscles that make up the back portion of your lower arm, between your elbow and wrist.</p></p>
                                </div>
